		<div class="comment-body"><p>@Jack</p>
<p>I agree with your &#8220;truths&#8221; but I can&#8217;t agree that they are truths and not opinion; especially the Salatin quote because it requires a definition of a good person, which absolutely deducts to opinion. </p>
<p>I agree with most of what you say, but when you start declaring truths, I can&#8217;t help but disagree with your definition of truth. Nearly anything can be disputed. I&#8217;m not going to call you arrogant, because I don&#8217;t think you are, but it *might* come across that way sometimes when your truths are declared. I&#8217;m guilty of it too, of course. But I suggest you avoid using that label and stick with &#8220;opinion&#8221;.</p>
</div>

