		<div class="comment-body"><p>Jack, if you were referring to the front yard vegetable garden of Julie Bass of Oak Park, Michigan, she was never actually put in jail. The city merely threatened her with jail time for the front yard garden. Then in July of 2011, when her blog (oakparkhatesveggies) brought her plight to international attention, the city began to get inundated with angry phone calls from around the world, some of them including death threats against city officials for being so ridiculous. So in July of 2011, the city dropped their case against her. Jail time never happened for her. (But they most definitely threatened her with jail time, and they were dead serious about it.)</p>
