		<div class="comment-body"><p>Your comment on the rocks capturing dew is correct, but time you listed is wrong.  The rocks carry the cold from the night into the morning and pull water out of the air via condensation -moist air on a cold surface.  The way I heard you on the show (about 37 minutes in) the rocks that are warm from the day pull in dew during the first part of the night, condensation will not form on the warmer surface.  I&#8217;m sure you know this and just had a brain cramp.</p>
